OL,3,CDenise Nolan pays tribute to late
OL,4,Csister Linda
OL,6,F"She was amazing, when it came to her
OL,7,Fdisease , I've never known anybody
OL,8,Flike her, she never showed it to me
OL,9,Fthat she was suffering" she told ITV's
OL,10,FGood Morning Britain (GMB).
OL,12,F"If she was having a bad day, she
OL,13,Fcalled it a duvet day, and she'd go to
OL,14,Fbed and stay in bed all day if she was
OL,15,Fhaving a bad day.
OL,17,F"She never let me see that side of
OL,18,Fher, as I said. If she wasn't feeling
OL,19,Fwell, she would go up to her room and
OL,20,Fthat was it. But most of the time she
OL,21,Fwas joking and laughing."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
